column15: Floresta de Campinarana. Arvore. Solo arenoso, dossel. DAP=12cm. Tronco circular. Sapopema concava a reta, assimetrica, A=C (20cm), não ramificada. Ritidoma marrom, rigido, levemente verrucoso (quase liso), desprendimento pulverulento. Lenticelas pouco salientes, esbranquicadas, <1mm comp., poucas, agrupadas irregularmente. Casca Morta marrom, <1mm espess. Casca Vivavermelha, 3mm espess., fibrosa, odor suave (lembra manga). Alburno cremeamarelado. Resina na cv, esbranquicada, opaca, mediana, pegajosa. Resina branca nos ramos. Frutos verde-amarelados quando jovens, vinaceos quando maduros. Sementes com arilo branco. Planta fichada: 1693-08
column16: Forest of Campinarana. Tree. Sandy soil, canopy. DAP = 12cm. Circular trunk. Sapopema concava the line, asymmetric, A = C (20cm), unbranched. Ritidoma brown, rigid, slightly verrucous (almost smooth), powdery detachment. Lenticelas slightly protruding, whitish, <1mm comp., Few, irregularly grouped. Brown dead skin, <1mm thick. Bark Bright, 3mm thick, fibrous, mild odor (reminiscent of mango). Creamy white albumin. Resin in cv, whitish, opaque, medium, sticky. White resin on the branches. Yellowish-green fruits when young, vinaceous when ripe. Seeds with white aril. Plant signed: 1693-08

column16: Nouragues Station - Bassin de l'Arataye. Long. 52°42 ', Lat. 4°3 'N Primary forest; Tree V-363. 23.3 cm Floral buttons Young fluted clear axes. Rib I slightly protruding sup. and very prominent face inf. Ribs II filiform sup. and prominent face inf. Young axillary inflorescences of the last leaves of the axes. In buttons.

column15: Guyane Française, Station de la Piste de St. Elie (ECEREX), km 15,7; 53°3'O, 5°17'N, Forêt primaire Abre DBH:33,4cm Phenologie: Sterile, Abre à contreforts étroits; bonne odeur d' encens à la coupe. Feuilles composées de 13 à 19 folioles; petiole plat face supérieure. Petiole et rachis lenticellés, courts petiolules. Limbre does folioles acuminé, discolore, base asymétrique, atteignant 13 x 4.5 cm. Nervure I jaunâtre peusaillante face supérieure et tres saillante face inferieure. Nervures II deprimees dessus, en arceaux réunis avant la marge., Collecte pour etude contrforts (M. Fournier, Engref Kourou)
column16: French Guiana, St. Elie Trail Station (ECEREX), km 15.7; 53°3'W, 5°17'N, Primary Forest Abre DBH: 33.4cm Phenology: Sterile, Abre with narrow buttresses; good smell of incense at the cut. Leaves composed of 13 to 19 leaflets; petiole flat top side. Petiole and lenticellate rachis, short petiolules. Leafless leaflets acuminate, discolored, asymmetric base, up to 13 x 4.5 cm. Ribbed yellowish vein with superior surface and very prominent underside. Ribs II depressed above, in arches united before the margin., Collection for contrasts (M. Fournier, Engref Kourou)
